[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7455,
        "end_time": 11936,
        "text": "In 1898, Marie and Pierre Curie \ndiscovered radium."
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 11936,
        "end_time": 14005,
        "text": "Claimed to have restorative properties,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 14005,
        "end_time": 15786,
        "text": "radium was added to toothpaste,"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 15786,
        "end_time": 16657,
        "text": "medicine,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 16657,
        "end_time": 17418,
        "text": "water,"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 17418,
        "end_time": 18615,
        "text": "and food."
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 18615,
        "end_time": 20486,
        "text": "A glowing, luminous green,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 20486,
        "end_time": 24007,
        "text": "it was also used in beauty products\nand jewelry."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 24007,
        "end_time": 26297,
        "text": "It wasn&#39;t until the mid-20th century"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 26297,
        "end_time": 30265,
        "text": "we realized that radium&#39;s harmful\neffects as a radioactive element"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 30265,
        "end_time": 32956,
        "text": "outweighed its visual benefits."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 32956,
        "end_time": 35876,
        "text": "Unfortunately, radium isn&#39;t the only\npigment that historically"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 35876,
        "end_time": 38585,
        "text": "seemed harmless or useful"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 38585,
        "end_time": 40535,
        "text": "but turned out to be deadly."
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 40535,
        "end_time": 44037,
        "text": "That lamentable distinction includes\na trio of colors and pigments"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 44037,
        "end_time": 47235,
        "text": "that we&#39;ve long used to decorate ourselves\nand the things we make:"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 47235,
        "end_time": 48116,
        "text": "white,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 48116,
        "end_time": 48817,
        "text": "green,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 48817,
        "end_time": 51726,
        "text": "and orange."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 51726,
        "end_time": 53777,
        "text": "Our story begins with white."
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 53777,
        "end_time": 56167,
        "text": "As far back as the 4th century BCE,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 56167,
        "end_time": 61397,
        "text": "the Ancient Greeks treated lead to make\nthe brilliant white pigment we know today."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 61397,
        "end_time": 62309,
        "text": "The problem?"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 62309,
        "end_time": 65938,
        "text": "In humans, lead is directly absorbed\ninto the body"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 65938,
        "end_time": 67368,
        "text": "and distributed to the blood,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 67368,
        "end_time": 68217,
        "text": "soft tissues,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 68217,
        "end_time": 70568,
        "text": "and mineralized tissues."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 70568,
        "end_time": 71917,
        "text": "Once in the nervous system,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 71917,
        "end_time": 75177,
        "text": "lead mimics and disrupts the normal\nfunctions of calcium,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 75177,
        "end_time": 77767,
        "text": "causing damages ranging \nfrom learning disabilities"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 77767,
        "end_time": 81079,
        "text": "to high blood pressure."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 81079,
        "end_time": 83578,
        "text": "Yet the practice \nof using this toxic pigment"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 83578,
        "end_time": 86670,
        "text": "continued across time and cultures."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 86670,
        "end_time": 90858,
        "text": "Lead white was the only practical choice\nfor white oil or tempera paint"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 90858,
        "end_time": 92908,
        "text": "until the 19th century."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 92908,
        "end_time": 97019,
        "text": "To make their paint, artists would grind\na block of lead into powder,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 97019,
        "end_time": 100088,
        "text": "exposing highly toxic dust particles."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 100088,
        "end_time": 104288,
        "text": "The pigment&#39;s liberal use resulted\nin what was known as painter&#39;s colic,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 104288,
        "end_time": 107528,
        "text": "or what we&#39;d now call lead poisoning."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 107528,
        "end_time": 110198,
        "text": "Artists who worked with lead complained\nof palseys,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 110198,
        "end_time": 111159,
        "text": "melancholy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 111159,
        "end_time": 112039,
        "text": "coughing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 112039,
        "end_time": 113140,
        "text": "enlarged retinas,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 113140,
        "end_time": 116758,
        "text": "and even blindness."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 116758,
        "end_time": 119929,
        "text": "But lead white&#39;s density, opacity,\nand warm tone"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 119929,
        "end_time": 124771,
        "text": "were irresistible to artists like Vermeer,\nand later, the Impressionists."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 124771,
        "end_time": 126402,
        "text": "Its glow couldn&#39;t be matched,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 126402,
        "end_time": 131659,
        "text": "and the pigment continued to be widely\nused until it was banned in the 1970s."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 131659,
        "end_time": 133271,
        "text": "As bad as all that sounds,"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 133271,
        "end_time": 135770,
        "text": "white&#39;s dangerous effects \npale in comparison"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 135770,
        "end_time": 140191,
        "text": "to another, \nmore wide-spread pigment, green."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 140191,
        "end_time": 144110,
        "text": "Two synthetic greens called \nScheele&#39;s Green and Paris Green"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 144110,
        "end_time": 147831,
        "text": "were first introduced in the 18th century."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 147831,
        "end_time": 150020,
        "text": "They were far more vibrant and flashy"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 150020,
        "end_time": 153241,
        "text": "than the relatively dull greens\nmade from natural pigments,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 153241,
        "end_time": 155620,
        "text": "so they quickly became popular choices\nfor paint"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 155620,
        "end_time": 157630,
        "text": "as well as dye for textiles,"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 157630,
        "end_time": 158630,
        "text": "wallpaper,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 158630,
        "end_time": 159473,
        "text": "soaps,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 159473,
        "end_time": 160500,
        "text": "cake decorations,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 160500,
        "end_time": 161290,
        "text": "toys,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 161290,
        "end_time": 162071,
        "text": "candy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 162071,
        "end_time": 163661,
        "text": "and clothing."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 163661,
        "end_time": 166232,
        "text": "These green pigments were made from\na compound called"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 166232,
        "end_time": 168641,
        "text": "cupric hydrogen arsenic."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 168641,
        "end_time": 170509,
        "text": "In humans, exposure to arsenic"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 170509,
        "end_time": 173759,
        "text": "can damage the way cells \ncommunicate and function."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 173759,
        "end_time": 176239,
        "text": "And high levels of arsenic have been\ndirectly linked"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 176239,
        "end_time": 178600,
        "text": "to cancer and heart disease."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 178600,
        "end_time": 183421,
        "text": "As a result, 18th century fabric\nfactory workers were often poisoned,"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 183421,
        "end_time": 186582,
        "text": "and women in green dresses \nreportedly collapsed"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 186582,
        "end_time": 189622,
        "text": "from exposure to arsenic on their skin."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 189622,
        "end_time": 192541,
        "text": "Bed bugs were rumored not to live\nin green rooms,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 192541,
        "end_time": 196852,
        "text": "and it&#39;s even been speculated that\nNapoleon died from slow arsenic poisoning"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 196852,
        "end_time": 200851,
        "text": "from sleeping in his green \nwallpapered bedroom."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 200851,
        "end_time": 204370,
        "text": "The intense toxicity of these green\nstayed under wraps"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 204370,
        "end_time": 208153,
        "text": "until the arsenic recipe was published\nin 1822."
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 208153,
        "end_time": 212022,
        "text": "And a century later, it was repurposed\nas an insecticide."
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 212022,
        "end_time": 216403,
        "text": "Synthetic green was probably the most\ndangerous color in widespread use,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 216403,
        "end_time": 219833,
        "text": "but at least it didn&#39;t share radium&#39;s\nproperty of radioactivity."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 219833,
        "end_time": 223093,
        "text": "Another color did, though - orange."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 223093,
        "end_time": 227293,
        "text": "Before World War II, it was common\nfor manufacturers of ceramic dinnerware"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 227293,
        "end_time": 230443,
        "text": "to use uranium oxide in colored glazes."
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 230443,
        "end_time": 232974,
        "text": "The compound produced brilliant\nreds and oranges,"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 232974,
        "end_time": 237234,
        "text": "which were appealing attributes,\nif not for the radiation they emitted."
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 237234,
        "end_time": 241693,
        "text": "Of course, radiation was something\nwe were unaware of until the late 1800s,"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 241693,
        "end_time": 246460,
        "text": "let alone the associated cancer risks,\nwhich we discovered much later."
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 246460,
        "end_time": 247754,
        "text": "During World War II,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 247754,
        "end_time": 252583,
        "text": "the U.S. government confiscated all uranium\nfor use in bomb development."
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 252583,
        "end_time": 257805,
        "text": "However, the atomic energy commission\nrelaxed these restrictions in 1959,"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 257805,
        "end_time": 262444,
        "text": "and depleted uranium returned to ceramics\nand glass factory floors."
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 262444,
        "end_time": 264395,
        "text": "Orange dishes made during \nthe next decade"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 264395,
        "end_time": 268264,
        "text": "may still have some hazardous qualities\non their surfaces to this day."
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 268264,
        "end_time": 273045,
        "text": "Most notably, vintage fiestaware\nreads positive for radioactivity."
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 273045,
        "end_time": 276975,
        "text": "And while the levels are low enough that\nthey don&#39;t officially pose a health risk"
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 276975,
        "end_time": 278584,
        "text": "if they&#39;re on a shelf,"
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 278584,
        "end_time": 284159,
        "text": "the U.S. EPA warns against eating food\noff of them."
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 284159,
        "end_time": 288034,
        "text": "Though we still occasionally run \ninto issues with synthetic food dyes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 288034,
        "end_time": 293135,
        "text": "our scientific understanding has helped us\nprune hazardous colors out of our lives."
    }
]